{\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{\sqrt{n}}\sin\left(nx\right)}
x\in\left[0,2\pi\right]
{\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\sin\left(nx\right)}
n \in \mathbb{N}
x\neq 2 \pi k 
k \in \mathbb{Z}
 \sin(kx)=\frac{\cos\bigl((k-\frac{1}{2})x\bigr)-\cos\bigl((k+\frac{1}{2})x\bigr)}{2\sin\frac{x}{2}}
\left|\sum_{k=1}^n \sin(kx)\right|\leq\left|\frac{1}{\sin\frac{x}{2}}\right|
